Class MessageQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • MessageQueue

  • public class MessageQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    This class creates a queue (FIFO) as a linked list using MessageListNodes. The queue keeps track of its first and last node, so that the add, remove, peek, and isEmpty are all O(1). The queue just has the required queue functions: the constructor, add(), remove(), isEmpty() and peek().
    Author:
    AnneMarie Caballero (annemariecabs)
